# Production build config — consumed by `npm run build` (Vite production mode).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are PUBLISHABLE values only: the project URL and the anon/publishable
# key. They are safe in the client bundle BY DESIGN — Row Level Security is the
# real boundary (see src/lib/supabaseClient.js and .env.example). They are
# committed so the GitHub Actions Android build bakes in real Supabase config;
# without them the bundle ships `createClient(undefined, undefined)`, which
# throws at module load and boots the Capacitor WebView to a black screen.
#
# Render keeps its own dashboard env vars, which take precedence over this file
# on that platform — so this changes nothing for the web deploy, it only feeds
# the CI/native build that had no env at all.
#
# REAL secrets (BBF_ADMIN_TOKEN, coach-agent tokens, service-role keys) are NEVER
# build-time vars — they stay runtime-injected per CLAUDE.md §7. Do not add them here.
